Quality lesson! I found this at one of my local dispensaries the other day, so I figured I’d take a second to educate NEW glass buyers in the industry😄 Clearly, this piece is an import, most likely from China. There are a couple ways you can tell: 1. The inner most tube in that crappy perc isn’t flame polished! It was scored, snapped, and inserted without taking the few seconds to polish out the little imperfections. Yuck 🤢2. Judging by where the perc holes are in relation to the center tube, I doubt this will function properly. Function is all about ratios. 📐🧮 3. The color patterning is painted on the glass! This could be harmful in the long run because these are typically cheap paints that are toxic to humans 🤮 I literally chipped paint off this tube with my thumbnail. 🤔🤔 I get it, glass made in America is more expensive, but you’ll be a lot happier with the quality and longevity of your piece, in addition to the health benefits associated with buying a piece that uses colored glass, instead of toxic paints you’ll be putting yer face on. I literally laughed when I saw this garbage 😂 This belongs in the trash 🗑 #buyamerican and don’t let me catch you using something like this😪 #garbage #piecesoverprofits
